/* MCDI version 1
 *
 * Each MCDI request starts with an MCDI_HEADER, which is a 32bit
 * काष्ठाure, filled in by the client.
 *
 *       0       7  8     16    20     22  23  24    31
 *      | CODE | R | LEN | SEQ | Rsvd | E | R | XFLAGS |
 *               |                      |   |
 *               |                      |   \--- Response
 *               |                      \------- Error
 *               \------------------------------ Resync (always set)
 *
 * The client ग_लिखोs it's request पूर्णांकo MC shared memory, and rings the
 * करोorbell. Each request is completed by either by the MC writting
 * back पूर्णांकo shared memory, or by writting out an event.
 *
 * All MCDI commands support completion by shared memory response. Each
 * request may also contain additional data (accounted क्रम by HEADER.LEN),
 * and some response's may also contain additional data (again, accounted
 * क्रम by HEADER.LEN).
 *
 * Some MCDI commands support completion by event, in which any associated
 * response data is included in the event.
 *
 * The protocol requires one response to be delivered क्रम every request, a
 * request should not be sent unless the response क्रम the previous request
 * has been received (either by polling shared memory, or by receiving
 * an event).
 */

